# AI product standards

## Role of the model

Use models for **judgment-heavy** text and **nuanced extraction**; use **code** for **money, eligibility, scoring math, and CRM writes**. Never let free-form text be the only record of budget or stage.

## Structure

- Outputs should map to **validated fields** (currency, zone, timeline buckets)—see lead-qualification skill for shapes.
- **Recommendations** pair **ranked listing refs** with **short rationale** tied to buyer constraints—not undifferentiated lists.

## Control

- Configurable **policies per agency/channel**: drafts, approvals, tone, when to escalate to a human broker.

## Measurement

- Log retrievable metadata for debugging and regression: **template/version**, **tool calls**, **scores**, not full PII in hot paths.
- Critical paths need **evaluation hooks** before prompt changes ship: qualification accuracy, match relevance, handoff quality.

## Bar

Ship features that improve **visit booking**, **stage progression**, or **operator time-to-action**—not demos where “the AI replied.”
